  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "As discussed with @hwwhww on Discord there seems to be a problem related to PR #3126. [The new test]( https://media.githubusercontent.com/media/ethereum/consensus-spec-tests/master/tests/mainnet/bellatrix/sync/optimistic/pyspec_tests/from_syncing_to_invalid/steps.yaml) uses the same `block_hash` for different branches, particularly `0x376f20f22f880c3be5a8c360f8ff86941e6aa5fac3b5de7825d2efee3f70e891`, `0x2e0f73c5b1489715b161e0c11af557c8ac758c3b99aed6744bbbbe73687beb38`, `0x6c59e0eb4b2de1a922c639c12f6a0528c672f69d388bff4f7dbbad261ab12bee`. This should not happen under normal behavior. [The previous test version](https://media.githubusercontent.com/media/ethereum/consensus-spec-tests/v1.2.0/tests/mainnet/bellatrix/sync/optimistic/pyspec_tests/from_syncing_to_invalid/steps.yaml) used different `block_hash`es. We found this by updating Grandine, but other clients may not be affected as they may be ignoring `block_hash` (at least Prysm according to @potuz).",
